<paragraph id="8BA98874FFE3FF9B718738D37CA4FE03" blockId="11.[151,1436,222,499]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452">
Known from two localities in the western part of the Eastern Cape Province, and a number of sites in the far southwest of the Western Cape (
<bibRefCitation id="EF87F585FFE3FF9B7310390E7E5AFEEB" author="Bistrom" box="[512,794,258,283]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452" refString="Bistrom, O. &amp; Nilsson, A. N. (2006) Taxonomic revision of the Ethiopian genus Canthyporus (Coleoptera Dytiscidae). Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 85, 209 - 306. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4081 / memorieSEI. 2006.209" type="journal article" year="2006">
Biström &amp; Nilsson 
<number id="3DDE9A53FFE3FF9B73CD390E7E5AFEEB" box="[733,794,258,283]" pageId="11" pageNumber="452" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). I can add the following records, which extend the range far to the north, into the Northern Cape. This species can be found in running water, but in my experience is most abundant in shallow mossy swamps, with or without seepage flow: 
